   whether that localized bit is turned on or off.

3. Bit Difference Logic (Hamming Distance):
   The XOR (^) operator compares two integer bit streams and assigns a '1' output 
   only to indices where the two source values disagree. Iterating through the 
   XOR footprint via right shifts keeps track of the absolute positional variant count.

